What you need to know:

Chirchir, the chairman of Sigowet Community Demand Driven Committee, a farming group, says he went for bananas as a business because the crop does not require much capital.The full-time farmer has staggered his crops to ensure they mature at different times so that he earns throughout the year.His long-term goal is to add value to the bananas by ripening and making crisps. Â Tissue culture bananas are tolerant to diseases and drought, ensuring farmers earn more.